##Shuanghuanglian: The business experience and secret past of "pneumonia miracle drug"

Weixin Guokr233

Function introduction, new media of Science and technology industry under the fruit shell. We focus on technology, companies, industries, and people related to new technologies, as reporters, observers, and learners "from the lab to the industrial market. ".

After the Spring Festival, the new crown pneumonia continues to show its unpleasant side: The stock market under the shadow of the epidemic presents a double-day spectacle of ice and fire: Over there, nearly 3,000 individual stocks fell by the daily limit on the first day of trading, this side of the Chamber is the pharmaceutical company stock price high Jinmen have increased by the daily trading limit.

The concept of vaccines, masks and other stocks rose in reason, this round of surging market also has a not surprising booster as "dual-coptis. ".

Blow up the foam of Shuanghuanglian
On January 31, the People's Daily revealed that a team of researchers from the Wuhan Virus Institute and the Shanghai Institute of Medicine of the Chinese Academy of Sciences had demonstrated in vitro laboratory experiments that Shuanghuanglian had an inhibitory effect on COVID-19, further clinical studies are needed to confirm this.
The ability to carry goods depends on it

News triggered a nationwide buying frenzy, leading directly to Shuanghuanglian Line on-line and off-line instantaneous goods.

Shuanghuanglian and its research institutions, Wuhan Institute of Virology and Shanghai Institute of Medicine, have been severely criticized by scientific research and medical workers, but this did not prevent the two days after the market fanaticism Shuanghuanglian. Magnifier team (ID: Guokr233) noted: February 3 and 4, "Shuanghuanglian concept stock" Harbin pharmaceutical shares, Tai Long Pharmaceutical trading. Hong Kong shares of Forson Pharmaceutical, 3 the day's shares rose as much as 230% , closing up 41.11% .

Why did the share prices of these companies skyrocket? Hengrui, one of the top domestic drug companies, had a dynamic price-earnings ratio of 75.9 times on Feb. 3, compared with about 80 times for both tailong and Fusen, the dynamic price-earnings ratio of Harbin pharmaceutical shares is a staggering 1,969.90 times.

Foam is a bitch. The price-earnings ratio is a crude measure.

The medicine came from outside the gate

What is Shuanghuanglian? What's so special about it? Where did it come from? And what kind of trajectory has it gone through?

Shuanghuanglian by honeysuckle (Shuanghua) , scutellaria and Forsythia three compatibility of Chinese medicine, cut from the Qing Dynasty Epidemic Febrile Disease Scientist Wu Tang "differentiation of Epidemic Febrile Diseases" of "Yinqiaosan.

Shuanghuanglian is not old, but in the existing network information, can not accurately point out who exactly, when developed this now well-known recipe. The history of Shuanghuanglian prescription in literature shows that it came into being in the northeast of China during the Cultural Revolution ———————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————— --.

In another propaganda document from Henan Tailong (one of the main manufacturers of Shuanghuanglian oral liquid) , it was introduced that Shuanghuanglian decoction originated during the war period, and later, in order to solve the shortage of medicines, it was made into injections and was widely used in rural clinics by itinerant medical teams during the Cultural Revolution.

In the early 1970s, the Second Affiliated Hospital of the Harbin Medical University made sterile powder injections 1 from three traditional Chinese medicines. In May 1976, at the "live meeting of Chinese Herbal Medicine Exchange" held in Heilongjiang, Hegang promoted the use of Shuanghuanglian injection in the treatment of pediatric pneumonia 2.

For the next 30 years, Shuanghuanglian had deep relations with Heilongjiang and even the northeast.

Searching the database of China Knowledge Network (Chn) , we can find that since 1977, for 15 years, almost all of the theses, including the thesis on Veterinary Medicine —————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————— --. One of the earliest papers was a clinical paper on the use of Shuanghuanglian injection in the treatment of pneumonia in children. (over time, Shuanghuanglian and several other commonly used proprietary Chinese medicine injections have been banned in infants and young children.).

From 1977 to 1992, most of the papers on "Shuanghuanglian" were written in Heilongjiang

It is worth noting that the "anti-virus research" conducted by the Shanghai Institute of Medicine and Wuhan Institute of Virology is not the first. As early as the late 1980s, the anti-virus experiment of Shuanghuanglian injection had already been published, one of the papers, entitled Experimental Study of Shuanghuanglian Oral Liquid against human respiratory syncytial virus, was cited by academician Zhong Nanshan in two papers around 2005. In addition, the paper on allergic reaction induced by Shuanghuanglian injection was also briefly reported as early as 1991

"However, I have not found any allergic reaction to Shuanghuanglian injection in the information I have reviewed, so I reported it to attract the attention of my colleagues. "

When is Shuanghuanglian out of the northeast, towards the national?

1992, a special year. In this year, the first batch of provincial Shuanghuanglian clinical case papers were published, these papers from Shandong, Anhui and other hospitals, using Harbin No. 2 factory of Traditional Chinese medicine production of "Shuanghuanglian powder injection" , carried out hundreds of clinical applications.

It may be that Shuanghuanglian has come out of Shanhai Pass, partly because production problems have been solved, as it was in the early 1990s, when two key batch numbers appeared in several papers: made by the Heilongjiang Drug Laboratory, shuanghuanglian oral solution with batch number 890324, and Shuanghuanglian injection with batch number 900616, produced by Harbin No. 2 Traditional Chinese Medicine Factory.

And it is this powder injection, but also brought another reason: In a 1992 Shanghai Hospital paper 7, mentioned a likely to make Shuanghuanglian to the national event: the First Shuanghuanglian powder injection academic seminar.
Section 7 of Shuanghuanglian for treatment of respiratory tract infection

This may be an early example of pharmaceutical marketing or "academic promotion" . The collection of essays can even be bought today on the secondhand book website for 26 yuan for cabbage.

Why 1992?

Harbin Pharmaceutical Group was reorganized in 1991, Harbin Pharmaceutical Holding Company entered the capital market, Harbin No. 2 Traditional Chinese Medicine Factory was just one of the pharmaceutical factories merged into Harbin pharmaceutical group when Harbin Pharmaceutical Group was founded in 1988, and became a subsidiary company of Harbin Pharmaceutical Holding Company after restructuring in 1991. Later, Harbin Pharmaceutical Holdings became the first Chinese pharmaceutical company to go public.

Since then, Shuanghuanglian began to stride towards the national.

Shuanghuanglian injection has created many first, the first pure powder injection for intravenous use of Chinese medicine, but also China's first listed pharmaceutical company's important products. But the market is relentless, out of Shanhai Pass's Shuanghuanglian, but also to experience the test of the market.

Henan: Learner, Poacher and competitor

Shuanghuanglian started its career in northeast China, and has become the key star product of the local pharmaceutical enterprises. So far, the State Food and Drug Administration approved 85 Chinese Medicine Zhunzihao Shuanghuanglian preparations, the northeast took 36, and a province in Heilongjiang accounted for 32.

Shuanghuanglian has laid the foundation for the rise of Harbin Pharmaceutical Group, but production of Shuanghuanglian in other regions, such as Henan, is also rapidly catching up.

Henan Province has won 9 Shuanghuanglian preparation of the Chinese characters, also has honeysuckle authentic Real Estate Xinmi. The result was two publicly listed drug companies that started out as Shuanghuanglian: Zhengzhou's Tailong pharmaceutical and Xichuan's Fusen Pharmaceutical.

Probably inspired by the "first seminar on Shuanghuanglian injection powder" held by Harbin No. 2 Traditional Chinese Medicine Factory in 1992, Shuanghuanglian pharmaceutical enterprises have been established in Henan Province. Tailong pharmaceutical (formerly known as Zhengzhou Zhulin Zhongsheng) was founded in 1993. It acquired the right to transfer Shuanghuanglian oral liquid from Harbin No. 4 factory of Traditional Chinese medicine and hired its chief engineer, Xing Zetian (who was also the first patent inventor of Shuanghuanglian oral liquid) , started the production business of Shuanghuanglian oral liquid; Fusen Pharmaceutical (formerly Xichuan Pharmaceutical) was founded in 1995; and Henan Tiandi Pharmaceutical, another pharmaceutical company based in Kaifeng, Henan, was founded in 1997, in addition to producing Xingnaojing injection, it also produces Shuanghuanglian oral liquid (now 60 per cent owned by listed company Tasly Group) .

Strong demand on the b-side of the market has led to rising acquisition prices for honeysuckle. The most painful is Harbin pharmaceutical shares, from 2016, Harbin pharmaceutical shares in three consecutive years in the annual report, big talk about the problem of high prices of the original medicinal materials. The chart below shows the price trend of the crude drug in Harbin Pharmaceutical Co.'s 2018 annual report. The price of honeysuckle rose from 80 yuan / kg in 2016 to a high of over 180 yuan / kg in 2018.
Harbin pharmaceutical shares in the 2018 financial report in the original price trend of medicinal materials, data from the Netcom

In fact, the rally did not stop, magnifier team (ID: Guokr233) Query Medicine Tongnet data found that in early February 2020, the most inferior honeysuckle (Baihua) acquisition price has reached 175 yuan / kg, and the best blue and white up to 280 yuan / kg.

The original medicinal materials prices for three consecutive years, Shuanghuanglian oral liquid sales decline, resulting in a recession in the entire industry. In 2017 and 2018, the output of Shuanghuanglian oral liquid dropped by 17% and 4.71% respectively. On January 22,2020, Harbin pharmaceutical stock issued the "announcement on the reduction of annual performance of Harbin pharmaceutical stock in 2019" , 9 saying that net profit in 2019 is expected to decrease by 270 million yuan to 310 million yuan compared with the same period last year, a 78% to 90% decrease compared with the same period last year; Revenue of Shuanghuanglian oral solution and injection dropped by 21% to 44% , according to the 2019 half-yearly report of folsom pharmaceutical.

In the face of rising drug prices, drug companies are not waiting to die. In fact, Shuanghuanglian producers have been trying to save themselves by changing their prescriptions since 2015.

I don't think anyone here has ever had an authentic Shuanghuanglian

Since 2015, Tai Long Pharmaceutical Co. and Harbin Pharmaceutical Co. have submitted applications to the National Pharmacopoeia Commission in an attempt to change the Flos Lonicerae in Shuanghuanglian oral solution / capsule prescriptions to Flos Lonicerae. The price of Flos Lonicerae from Hunan Province is only 90 to 105 yuan per kilogram (February 2020) , about half of the price of Flos Lonicerae, according to Yaotong. com. Therefore, the direct purpose of modifying the prescription is to reduce the production cost.

Notice on Application for change of Flos Lonicerae to Flos LONICERAE JAPONICAE in the prescription of "Shuanghuanglian oral liquid" of Henan Tailong Pharmaceutical Co. , Ltd. . 10, Source: official website of the National Pharmacopoeia Commission

Notice of changing honeysuckle to Flos Lonicerae in the prescription of "Shuanghuanglian capsule" of Harbin No. 4 Traditional Chinese Medicine Factory Co. , Ltd. . 11, from the official website of the National Pharmacopoeia Commission

But honeysuckle is the main ingredient of Shuanghuanglian originally, after revising the prescription, is Shuanghuanglian Still Shuanghuanglian?

In fact, the honeysuckle and honeysuckle fight has a long history. On August 12,2014, Lu Qun, an official with the Hunan Discipline Inspection Commission, posted a Weibo Post questioning the state PHARMACOPOEIA's move to rename the "southern honeysuckle" from Hunan Province as "mountain honeysuckle" , sparking a massive online debate.

But the debate did not give Hunan face. According to the 2015 edition of the Pharmacopoeia of the People's Republic of China, there is still only one source of medicine for Lonicerae JAPONICAE FLOS: The dry buds or first flowers of Lonicera Japonica thunb. 12.

The 2015 edition of the pharmacopoeia still lists Lonicera FLOS separately, they come from as many as four sources: Lonicera macranthoides hand.-mazz.Lonicera Hypoglauca, Lonicera Confusa DC. Or Lonicera Fultomentosa Lonicera Fulvotomentosa with dry buds or young flowers.

According to the 2015 edition of the National Pharmacopoeia, both Shuanghuanglian oral liquid 14 and Shuanghuanglian capsule 15 are used honeysuckle, not honeysuckle.

However, in addition to the manufacturers of Shuanghuanglian, there are Jiuzhitang, China resources 39(Huangshi) and other drug companies to change the prescription application. At present, Tai Long, Harbin Pharmaceutical Group official website of Shuanghuanglian manual is still using honeysuckle. If the revised prescription is included in the new edition of the PHARMACOPOEIA, these drug companies can legitimately switch to the production of Shuanghuanglian with honeysuckle.

But in fact, the unspoken rules still exist. According to Chinese Pharmacopoeia, the quality of honeysuckle is measured by chlorogenic acid. However, honeysuckle (i. e. honeysuckle) vine and leaf chlorogenic acid content, but higher than the flower bud medicine, so many pharmaceutical companies even give up the expensive honeysuckle, direct use of honeysuckle vine, leaf medicine. From the chlorogenic acid content test, this operation can not find fault.

Whether it is to switch to honeysuckle or honeysuckle vine leaves, it means that you may not be easy to drink the authentic Shuanghuanglian.

How long will the foam last?

Interestingly, on February 3, the same day that the trading limit was reached, Tai Long Pharmaceutical Company immediately issued the "notice on shareholders' plan to reduce their share holdings through concentrated bidding" 16, announcing that the company's second largest shareholder had adopted the method of concentrated bidding transaction, to reduce its shareholding in the company by no more than 1.05% of the company's total share capital. Although Tai Long Pharmaceutical Co. also alerted investors to the risks associated with the sell-off through the abnormal stock trading announcement, the a-share market appeared to be unimpressed by this kind of shareholder selling on the high side, and the sell-off announcement came the next morning, tai Lung Medicine up by the daily limit.

Harbin pharmaceutical shares also rose by the daily limit again. On February 4th the dynamic price earnings ratio of Harbin pharmaceutical shares reached a staggering 2,168.65 times. But the Hong kong-listed Company's shares were down 12.72 per cent at the close of trading on February 4.

Shuanghuanglian was born in the war years, and grew up in the northeast, and then throughout the country to blossom and bear fruit. But the original drug prices continued to rise, after the replacement can convince patients and the market, is still doubtful. So far, there is no evidence that Shuanghuanglian has a definite clinical effect on new coronary pneumonia. The a-share market ignores the facts and uses people's panic psychology to keep chasing the concept of Shuanghuanglian stocks. It is no different from continuing to build castles in the air and blow up bubbles.

When the fanatical profit-seeking mentality control people's minds, no matter how good medicine, no matter how clear-headed the popularization of science will be of no avail.

Shuanghuanglian has laid the foundation for the rise of Harbin Pharmaceutical Group, but production of Shuanghuanglian in other regions, such as Henan, is also rapidly catching up.

Henan Province has won 9 Shuanghuanglian preparation of the Chinese characters, also has honeysuckle authentic Real Estate Xinmi. The result was two publicly listed drug companies that started out as Shuanghuanglian: Zhengzhou's Tailong pharmaceutical and Xichuan's Fusen Pharmaceutical.

Probably inspired by the "first seminar on Shuanghuanglian injection powder" held by Harbin No. 2 Traditional Chinese Medicine Factory in 1992, Shuanghuanglian pharmaceutical enterprises have been established in Henan Province. Tailong pharmaceutical (formerly known as Zhengzhou Zhulin Zhongsheng) was founded in 1993. It acquired the right to transfer Shuanghuanglian oral liquid from Harbin No. 4 factory of Traditional Chinese medicine and hired its chief engineer, Xing Zetian (who was also the first patent inventor of Shuanghuanglian oral liquid) , started the production business of Shuanghuanglian oral liquid; Fusen Pharmaceutical (formerly Xichuan Pharmaceutical) was founded in 1995; and Henan Tiandi Pharmaceutical, another pharmaceutical company based in Kaifeng, Henan, was founded in 1997, in addition to producing Xingnaojing injection, it also produces Shuanghuanglian oral liquid (now 60 per cent owned by listed company Tasly Group) .

Strong demand on the b-side of the market has led to rising acquisition prices for honeysuckle. The most painful is Harbin pharmaceutical shares, from 2016, Harbin pharmaceutical shares in three consecutive years in the annual report, big talk about the problem of high prices of the original medicinal materials. The chart below shows the price trend of the crude drug in Harbin Pharmaceutical Co.'s 2018 annual report. The price of honeysuckle rose from 80 yuan / kg in 2016 to a high of over 180 yuan / kg in 2018.

In fact, the rally did not stop, magnifier team (ID: Guokr233) Query Medicine Tongnet data found that in early February 2020, the most inferior honeysuckle (Baihua) acquisition price has reached 175 yuan / kg, and the best blue and white up to 280 yuan / kg.

The original medicinal materials prices for three consecutive years, Shuanghuanglian oral liquid sales decline, resulting in a recession in the entire industry. In 2017 and 2018, the output of Shuanghuanglian oral liquid dropped by 17% and 4.71% respectively. On January 22,2020, Harbin pharmaceutical stock issued the "announcement on the reduction of annual performance of Harbin pharmaceutical stock in 2019" , 9 saying that net profit in 2019 is expected to decrease by 270 million yuan to 310 million yuan compared with the same period last year, a 78% to 90% decrease compared with the same period last year; Revenue of Shuanghuanglian oral solution and injection dropped by 21% to 44% , according to the 2019 half-yearly report of folsom pharmaceutical.

In the face of rising drug prices, drug companies are not waiting to die. In fact, Shuanghuanglian producers have been trying to save themselves by changing their prescriptions since 2015.

I don't think anyone here has ever had an authentic Shuanghuanglian

Since 2015, Tai Long Pharmaceutical Co. and Harbin Pharmaceutical Co. have submitted applications to the National Pharmacopoeia Commission in an attempt to change the Flos Lonicerae in Shuanghuanglian oral solution / capsule prescriptions to Flos Lonicerae. The price of Flos Lonicerae from Hunan Province is only 90 to 105 yuan per kilogram (February 2020) , about half of the price of Flos Lonicerae, according to Yaotong. com. Therefore, the direct purpose of modifying the prescription is to reduce the production cost.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Notice on Application for change of Flos Lonicerae to Flos LONICERAE JAPONICAE in the prescription of "Shuanghuanglian oral liquid" of Henan Tailong Pharmaceutical Co. , Ltd. . 10, Source: official website of the National Pharmacopoeia Commission

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Notice of changing honeysuckle to Flos Lonicerae in the prescription of "Shuanghuanglian capsule" of Harbin No. 4 Traditional Chinese Medicine Factory Co. , Ltd. . 11, from the official website of the National Pharmacopoeia Commission

But honeysuckle is the main ingredient of Shuanghuanglian originally, after revising the prescription, is Shuanghuanglian Still Shuanghuanglian?

In fact, the honeysuckle and honeysuckle fight has a long history. On August 12,2014, Lu Qun, an official with the Hunan Discipline Inspection Commission, posted a Weibo Post questioning the state PHARMACOPOEIA's move to rename the "southern honeysuckle" from Hunan Province as "mountain honeysuckle" , sparking a massive online debate.

But the debate did not give Hunan face. According to the 2015 edition of the Pharmacopoeia of the People's Republic of China, there is still only one source of medicine for Lonicerae JAPONICAE FLOS: The dry buds or first flowers of Lonicera Japonica thunb. 12.

The 2015 edition of the pharmacopoeia still lists Lonicera FLOS separately, they come from as many as four sources: Lonicera macranthoides hand.-mazz.Lonicera Hypoglauca, Lonicera Confusa DC. Or Lonicera Fultomentosa Lonicera Fulvotomentosa with dry buds or young flowers.

According to the 2015 edition of the National Pharmacopoeia, both Shuanghuanglian oral liquid 14 and Shuanghuanglian capsule 15 are used honeysuckle, not honeysuckle.

However, in addition to the manufacturers of Shuanghuanglian, there are Jiuzhitang, China resources 39(Huangshi) and other drug companies to change the prescription application. At present, Tai Long, Harbin Pharmaceutical Group official website of Shuanghuanglian manual is still using honeysuckle. If the revised prescription is included in the new edition of the PHARMACOPOEIA, these drug companies can legitimately switch to the production of Shuanghuanglian with honeysuckle.

But in fact, the unspoken rules still exist. According to Chinese Pharmacopoeia, the quality of honeysuckle is measured by chlorogenic acid. However, honeysuckle (i. e. honeysuckle) vine and leaf chlorogenic acid content, but higher than the flower bud medicine, so many pharmaceutical companies even give up the expensive honeysuckle, direct use of honeysuckle vine, leaf medicine. From the chlorogenic acid content test, this operation can not find fault.

Whether it is to switch to honeysuckle or honeysuckle vine leaves, it means that you may not be easy to drink the authentic Shuanghuanglian.

How long will the foam last?

Interestingly, on February 3, the same day that the trading limit was reached, Tai Long Pharmaceutical Company immediately issued the "notice on shareholders' plan to reduce their share holdings through concentrated bidding" 16, announcing that the company's second largest shareholder had adopted the method of concentrated bidding transaction, to reduce its shareholding in the company by no more than 1.05% of the company's total share capital. Although Tai Long Pharmaceutical Co. also alerted investors to the risks associated with the sell-off through the abnormal stock trading announcement, the a-share market appeared to be unimpressed by this kind of shareholder selling on the high side, and the sell-off announcement came the next morning, tai Lung Medicine up by the daily limit.

Harbin pharmaceutical shares also rose by the daily limit again. On February 4th the dynamic price earnings ratio of Harbin pharmaceutical shares reached a staggering 2,168.65 times. But the Hong kong-listed Company's shares were down 12.72 per cent at the close of trading on February 4.

Shuanghuanglian was born in the war years, and grew up in the northeast, and then throughout the country to blossom and bear fruit. But the original drug prices continued to rise, after the replacement can convince patients and the market, is still doubtful. So far, there is no evidence that Shuanghuanglian has a definite clinical effect on new coronary pneumonia. The a-share market ignores the facts and uses people's panic psychology to keep chasing the concept of Shuanghuanglian stocks. It is no different from continuing to build castles in the air and blow up bubbles.

When the fanatical profit-seeking mentality control people's minds, no matter how good medicine, no matter how clear-headed the popularization of science will be of no avail.
